WEBVTT

00:02.035 --> 00:04.137
(Charlie)
Previously on Graceland...

00:04.137 --> 00:05.672
- So you like it rough.
- Come on, mama.

00:05.672 --> 00:06.740
- [grunts]
- [groans]

00:06.740 --> 00:07.641
Oh shit.

00:07.641 --> 00:08.675
Secretly, I liked it.

00:08.675 --> 00:10.110
But next time,
maybe not so rough.

00:10.110 --> 00:11.512
I think I'm gonna be running

00:11.512 --> 00:13.514
everything that has to do
with the Sarkissian family.

00:13.514 --> 00:15.382
And I'm thinking
a great man can use

00:15.382 --> 00:17.651
a beautiful woman
by his side.

00:17.651 --> 00:19.086
(Charlie)
I want Germaine.

00:19.086 --> 00:20.153
If he tries to bolt,
don't be afraid

00:20.153 --> 00:21.755
to kick his ass
through a door.

00:21.755 --> 00:23.123
(Jakes)
Copy that.

00:23.123 --> 00:24.658
Somebody want to tell me
what the hell happened?

00:24.658 --> 00:26.226
He's an informant.

00:26.226 --> 00:27.261
(Jakes)
He's an informant for whom?

00:27.261 --> 00:29.096
(Charlie)
ATF.

00:29.096 --> 00:31.565
Look, the feds,
they have to have a mole,

00:31.565 --> 00:34.134
but you're never gonna know
until you ask.

00:34.134 --> 00:35.235
Ask who?

00:35.235 --> 00:37.671
Grab a federal agent,
tie his ass to a chair,

00:37.671 --> 00:39.706
and make him tell you
who the mole is.

00:39.706 --> 00:42.309
TLX119.

00:42.309 --> 00:43.410
Who you tailing?

00:43.410 --> 00:44.711
(Briggs)
One of the Sarkissians.

00:44.711 --> 00:48.048
(Logan)
Agent Warren,
what is Paul Briggs capable of?

00:48.048 --> 00:49.716
(Mike)
I wish I had more to tell you.

00:49.716 --> 00:52.185
If Paul's up to something,
it's news to me.

00:52.185 --> 00:55.188
[dramatic music]

00:55.188 --> 01:01.728
♪ ♪

01:10.571 --> 01:13.173
[door opens]

01:13.173 --> 01:14.408
[door shuts]

01:14.408 --> 01:17.444
[footsteps approaching]

01:17.444 --> 01:20.681
I know you've had
a hell of a day, Logan.

01:20.681 --> 01:23.750
But I'm gonna ask you
some questions.

01:23.750 --> 01:25.485
And I want you to exercise

01:25.485 --> 01:28.488
some sober reflection
before you answer me,

01:28.488 --> 01:31.224
because if you say
what I think you're gonna say,

01:31.224 --> 01:37.631
well, things are liable
to get a whole lot rougher.

01:41.068 --> 01:43.437
Are you gonna kill me?

01:45.472 --> 01:47.641
(Briggs)
You don't get to ask
the questions.

01:56.583 --> 01:58.218
What'd he say?
Anything?

01:58.218 --> 01:59.419
Well, nothing good.

01:59.419 --> 02:00.721
We just got to keep
working him over.

02:00.721 --> 02:02.122
He'll break.

02:02.122 --> 02:04.391
Nothing good:
phrase of the night.

02:04.391 --> 02:06.493
This has been
going on too long.

02:06.493 --> 02:07.995
You know what happens
if they catch us

02:07.995 --> 02:10.130
with the head
of Los Angeles FBI?

02:10.130 --> 02:12.366
Nothing good?

02:12.366 --> 02:13.600
It ain't no joke.

02:13.600 --> 02:15.235
We got to get rid of this guy
as soon as possible.

02:15.235 --> 02:18.505
Hey, Ari, the FBI
is up your ass, brother,

02:18.505 --> 02:20.507
and you don't know how far.

02:20.507 --> 02:21.575
Now, you want
to go in there

02:21.575 --> 02:23.076
and put a slug
in this guy's brain?

02:23.076 --> 02:25.512
Fine, let's do it,
but I think it's a waste.

02:25.512 --> 02:26.980
He's a source of information.

02:26.980 --> 02:28.248
We find out what he knows first,

02:28.248 --> 02:30.384
and then we bury him.

02:30.384 --> 02:32.352
I hate to see
a half-smoked cigarette

02:32.352 --> 02:34.988
on the ground.

02:34.988 --> 02:36.123
Okay.

02:36.123 --> 02:40.360
So frustrated, guy.

02:40.360 --> 02:43.163
Don't know what
I'm fighting for anymore.

02:43.163 --> 02:45.565
What do you mean?

02:45.565 --> 02:48.135
I talked to Tev.

02:48.135 --> 02:49.536
Martun is giving Toros

02:49.536 --> 02:51.738
his Artsiv yev Arryutsy
tomorrow.

02:51.738 --> 02:53.006
His Eagle and Lion?

02:53.006 --> 02:54.741
He shake hands,
kisses babies,

02:54.741 --> 02:56.677
receives
his initiation tattoos,

02:56.677 --> 02:58.345
and then it's over.

02:58.345 --> 02:59.646
Leadership is passed on.

02:59.646 --> 03:01.014
He is the new prince.

03:01.014 --> 03:04.418
That's bullshit, man.

03:04.418 --> 03:07.487
So you keep
working over our friend.

03:07.487 --> 03:10.357
I'm gonna go home
and get some sleep.

03:10.357 --> 03:11.358
You know what?

03:11.358 --> 03:12.626
I think we should
let him stew

03:12.626 --> 03:14.294
in his own filth
for a night.

03:14.294 --> 03:16.029
Maybe that'll loosen
his dumb ass up.

03:16.029 --> 03:17.130
You're sick, guy.

03:17.130 --> 03:18.432
I like it.

03:22.269 --> 03:26.173
Dale, get up.

03:26.173 --> 03:28.241
- Dale.
- Charlie, it's dark out.

03:28.241 --> 03:30.310
Listen, ATF won't let us
bust Germaine

03:30.310 --> 03:31.411
because they're building cases

03:31.411 --> 03:33.146
on all his gun-running clients,
right?

03:33.146 --> 03:34.414
What if we bag his ass

03:34.414 --> 03:36.316
without laying a finger
on their investigation?

03:36.316 --> 03:37.317
Mm-mm, I'm sleeping.

03:37.317 --> 03:38.652
No, you're not.
Get up. Come on.

03:38.652 --> 03:40.420
Why are you
bothering me?

03:40.420 --> 03:41.688
Because I want Germaine.

03:41.688 --> 03:43.590
Yeah, well, I want
a big house,

03:43.590 --> 03:44.725
I want a million dollars,

03:44.725 --> 03:46.159
and I want the love
of a beautiful woman.

03:46.159 --> 03:47.260
It's not in my cards.

03:47.260 --> 03:49.062
Then you need a new deck, boo.
Let's go.

03:49.062 --> 03:50.397
Listen, you're gonna go there.

03:50.397 --> 03:52.466
You're gonna tell Germaine that
the oxy business crapped out

03:52.466 --> 03:54.668
when the Windgates
got busted

03:54.668 --> 03:56.269
and that you want to get
into money laundering.

03:56.269 --> 03:58.171
I don't think Germaine
is taking interns, Charlie.

03:58.171 --> 03:59.539
Let me sleep.

03:59.539 --> 04:01.541
I'm not talking about an intern.
I'm talking about a buffer.

04:01.541 --> 04:02.542
ATF is protecting this guy.

04:02.542 --> 04:04.311
He knows that deal with ATF
is bullshit.

04:04.311 --> 04:05.512
One minute,
they got his back.

04:05.512 --> 04:06.713
Next minute,
they got him in cuffs.

04:06.713 --> 04:09.549
But what if he has someone else
doing his dirty work?

04:09.549 --> 04:11.084
You go in.
You meet his clients.

04:11.084 --> 04:12.319
You learn his network.

04:12.319 --> 04:13.587
The more you know
about his business,

04:13.587 --> 04:15.088
the easier it'll be.

04:15.088 --> 04:16.490
So you want me to become him?

04:16.490 --> 04:18.358
Yes, yes.

04:18.358 --> 04:20.761
Wheels up in two hours,
all right?

04:20.761 --> 04:22.095
Just...here.

04:22.095 --> 04:23.163
- Just--just get up.
- Don't--

04:23.163 --> 04:24.364
Let's get ready.

04:24.364 --> 04:30.270
♪ ♪

04:30.270 --> 04:33.273
[grunting]

04:35.542 --> 04:37.277
Hey, Paige.

04:37.277 --> 04:38.745
- Yeah.
- Have you seen Briggs?

04:38.745 --> 04:40.680
- No.
- Heard from him, anything?

04:40.680 --> 04:42.582
- Mm-mm.
- Shit.

04:42.582 --> 04:45.218
'Sup, bro?
What's going on?

04:45.218 --> 04:47.354
Briggs kidnapped Logan.

04:47.354 --> 04:48.555
What?

04:51.525 --> 04:52.626
What are you talking about?

04:52.626 --> 04:53.760
They grabbed him
off the street

04:53.760 --> 04:55.061
and threw him
in the back of a van.

04:55.061 --> 04:56.229
Wait, wait, wait,
who is they?

04:56.229 --> 04:57.664
I'm assuming Ari Adamian.

04:57.664 --> 05:00.634
No, no, he's not under
with the Sarkissians anymore,

05:00.634 --> 05:01.601
so no.

05:01.601 --> 05:02.969
Well, if Briggs grabbed Logan,

05:02.969 --> 05:04.437
he's got to have
a good reason for it, right?

05:04.437 --> 05:06.039
I know, and that's why
I haven't called this in.

05:06.039 --> 05:07.641
But I've been trying
to get ahold of him

05:07.641 --> 05:09.576
all night, all morning,
nothing.

05:09.576 --> 05:12.379
And if the SAC of the FBI
doesn't show up for work...

05:12.379 --> 05:13.647
Yeah, they're definitely
gonna notice it.

05:13.647 --> 05:15.515
I might need your help
with this one.

05:20.387 --> 05:21.488
Hi.

05:21.488 --> 05:25.592
Uh, guys,
I have a little problem.

05:27.394 --> 05:30.564
I kidnapped Agent Logan.

05:30.564 --> 05:31.698
(Briggs on recorder)
Ari pulled me in.

05:31.698 --> 05:32.999
He handed me a mask.

05:32.999 --> 05:35.001
I had no idea
where we were going.

05:35.001 --> 05:36.503
(Logan on recorder)
Bullshit.

05:36.503 --> 05:38.238
(Briggs on recorder)
I warned you, Logan.

05:38.238 --> 05:40.240
I told you they wanted
to question somebody.

05:40.240 --> 05:41.541
Remember that?

05:41.541 --> 05:42.676
They're trying to find out

05:42.676 --> 05:44.244
how deep
the federal investigation goes?

05:44.244 --> 05:46.012
Well, here we are.

05:46.012 --> 05:48.548
(Logan on recorder)
What do you want from me?

05:48.548 --> 05:50.283
I don't want shit, man.

05:50.283 --> 05:51.551
I didn't want this
in the first place.

05:51.551 --> 05:53.019
It wasn't my design.

05:53.019 --> 05:54.154
Then get me out.

05:54.154 --> 05:55.522
[scoffs]

05:55.522 --> 05:56.523
You want out?

05:56.523 --> 05:58.024
Okay, man,
I'll get you out.

05:58.024 --> 05:59.292
You say the word, Logan,

05:59.292 --> 06:00.994
and I'll shoot us
out of here right now.

06:00.994 --> 06:02.429
Matter of fact,
I'll do you one better.

06:02.429 --> 06:04.431
I'll call in the cavalry,
how's that, hmm?

06:04.431 --> 06:06.166
Tacked-out agents,
flash-bangs,

06:06.166 --> 06:07.567
birds in the sky,
the whole nine.

06:07.567 --> 06:10.136
But if we bring
Ari in now,

06:10.136 --> 06:14.241
we can't touch Martun,
and you and I both know it.

06:15.709 --> 06:18.011
[sighs]
Look.

06:18.011 --> 06:21.047
I have no idea how many people
have suffered for this case,

06:21.047 --> 06:22.449
but I do know this.

06:22.449 --> 06:24.251
Between Paige and myself,

06:24.251 --> 06:27.120
we have never been closer
to getting Martun Sarkissian

06:27.120 --> 06:29.723
than we are right now.

06:29.723 --> 06:32.058
We are so close.

06:32.058 --> 06:34.628
So you have a big decision
to make.

06:40.000 --> 06:42.636
You hold your cover.

06:42.636 --> 06:45.305
I want Martun.

06:45.305 --> 06:48.675
You do
whatever you have to do,

06:48.675 --> 06:51.044
but the second
you can get me out--

06:51.044 --> 06:52.646
the second--

06:52.646 --> 06:56.149
you do it.

06:56.149 --> 07:00.353
(Logan on recorder)
Paul, I do not
want to die here.

07:03.223 --> 07:05.492
Wow, Jesus Christ.

07:05.492 --> 07:07.093
Dude's got balls,
I'll give him that.

07:07.093 --> 07:08.628
(Mike)
Come on, Briggs.

07:08.628 --> 07:10.363
Ari isn't driving this.

07:10.363 --> 07:11.731
Three days ago
in your room,

07:11.731 --> 07:13.633
I heard you give Ari
Logan's plate number.

07:13.633 --> 07:17.070
[chuckles] No, Mike, that--
that's not what you heard.

07:17.070 --> 07:20.273
What you heard was Ari
giving me Logan's plate number.

07:20.273 --> 07:21.608
Listen, I know what I heard.

07:21.608 --> 07:24.477
Mike, you were about to vomit
your way through withdrawal.

07:24.477 --> 07:26.012
(Mike)
Yeah, that was before.

07:26.012 --> 07:29.716
You had a full-blown
psychotic breakdown, Mike.

07:37.257 --> 07:38.491
[sighs]

07:38.491 --> 07:41.995
Look, I know what I heard, okay?

07:41.995 --> 07:45.999
TLX119.

07:45.999 --> 07:47.968
That's what you said
on the phone.

07:47.968 --> 07:49.102
I didn't make it up.

07:49.102 --> 07:50.503
Yes, I did say that,
because I was repeating--

07:50.503 --> 07:51.738
I didn't make this up,
okay?

07:51.738 --> 07:53.573
I don't know what game
you're playing here,

07:53.573 --> 07:55.208
but whatever it is,
you don't have to--

07:55.208 --> 07:58.511
Mike, look in my eyes.

07:58.511 --> 08:00.347
This is not a game.

08:02.248 --> 08:05.251
[electronic music]

08:05.251 --> 08:11.424
♪ ♪

08:16.262 --> 08:17.184
(Paige)
What time does it start?

08:17.184 --> 08:20.967
(Toros)
It's tonight, but I want you
to come early.

08:21.001 --> 08:22.969
Mm-hmm, and who's
gonna be there?

08:23.003 --> 08:25.538
(Toros)
Leadership, important people.

08:25.572 --> 08:26.673
Well, sounds intimate.

08:26.673 --> 08:28.641
You sure it's not inappropriate
if I come?

08:28.675 --> 08:32.212
If it were inappropriate,
I wouldn't invite you.

08:32.245 --> 08:33.413
(Paige)
I mean, I don't know.

08:33.413 --> 08:34.681
(Toros)
Paige, I'm gonna ask you this now,

08:34.681 --> 08:36.683
one last and final time.

08:36.683 --> 08:40.687
Do you want to be
with me or not?

08:40.687 --> 08:43.490
(Paige)
Yes.

08:43.523 --> 08:45.558
If you're holding Logan here,

08:45.592 --> 08:47.660
we could set up
surveillance here.

08:47.694 --> 08:49.529
Yeah, looks like
a good vantage point, so...

08:49.562 --> 08:50.997
I don't know, guys.

08:51.031 --> 08:53.967
You got too many blind corners.
I can't take the risk.

08:54.000 --> 08:55.502
Even if Logan wants to stay
strapped to the chair all day,

08:55.535 --> 08:56.669
we should still
have a team in place.

08:56.669 --> 08:59.239
(Tuturro)
Yeah, at least
as a precaution, right?

08:59.272 --> 09:00.306
Well, hello.

09:00.340 --> 09:01.641
Did you not get the memo?

09:01.674 --> 09:04.044
We're gearing up for an op,
not a dinner party.

09:04.044 --> 09:05.178
Yeah, the Sarkissians
are having

09:05.211 --> 09:07.313
an initiation ceremony
for Toros tonight,

09:07.313 --> 09:09.449
and he wants me there,
so, uh...

09:09.449 --> 09:11.518
- What's that?
- It's a sort of a baptism.

09:11.551 --> 09:13.186
He's getting tattooed to show
his ascension

09:13.186 --> 09:15.455
into the Sarkissian
upper ranks.

09:15.455 --> 09:16.456
And you're gonna be
on his arm,

09:16.489 --> 09:19.192
so that makes you two,
what, a couple?

09:19.225 --> 09:20.727
I will be in the room
with Martun Sarkissian,

09:20.760 --> 09:24.364
so this is exactly what we've
been working towards, right?

09:27.600 --> 09:30.036
If it were any of the guys
in this position,

09:30.070 --> 09:31.438
no one would be
trying to stop him.

09:31.438 --> 09:32.439
- You know that, right?
- Didn't say anything.

09:32.439 --> 09:34.140
(Mike)
No, she's right.

09:34.174 --> 09:36.443
If you lock in your cover
with Toros tonight,

09:36.476 --> 09:38.645
there's no strategic advantage
to keeping Ari in play.

09:38.678 --> 09:41.614
(Tuturro)
True.

09:41.614 --> 09:43.349
She's gonna be
at the ceremony.

09:43.349 --> 09:44.751
We should move in now.

09:44.751 --> 09:46.186
No, Mike,
it's all unstable ground

09:46.219 --> 09:47.353
with the Sarkissians.

09:47.353 --> 09:49.089
We wait till Toros
gets his tattoos.

09:49.089 --> 09:50.190
- That's when we move.
- Okay.

09:50.223 --> 09:52.358
Okay.

09:52.358 --> 09:54.427
Then Logan just needs to survive
the night with you and Ari.

09:54.461 --> 09:57.097
Yeah. Yeah, I need you two
to stay tight to Toros.

09:57.130 --> 09:58.231
For what?

09:58.231 --> 09:59.499
(Paige)
This ceremony is at a church

09:59.499 --> 10:00.633
with little kids
and old ladies.

10:00.667 --> 10:01.734
I don't need babysitters
for this.

10:01.968 --> 10:03.470
(Briggs)
Come on, Paige, it's not that.

10:03.470 --> 10:05.205
I mean, look,
I can handle Ari on my own,

10:05.205 --> 10:06.473
but with Toros,
it's a tightrope.

10:06.473 --> 10:08.608
He'd put a bullet in Logan
just to spite me.

10:08.608 --> 10:11.578
(Tuturro)
Okay, so we make sure
Toros doesn't head your way.

10:11.611 --> 10:12.712
And as soon as he gets tatted,

10:12.745 --> 10:14.280
you call in a team,
get Logan out.

10:14.314 --> 10:16.349
The very moment.

10:16.382 --> 10:17.484
See you tonight.

10:17.484 --> 10:19.352
- All right.
- Bye.

10:23.756 --> 10:26.993
Anything else
we should know about?

10:26.993 --> 10:29.129
No, Mike, the plan's
all on the table.

10:33.133 --> 10:41.040
♪ ♪

10:42.475 --> 10:43.643
(Jakes)
I know you hate the humidity,

10:43.643 --> 10:45.745
but South Florida ain't bad.

10:45.979 --> 10:47.247
It's like living
in somebody's crotch.

10:47.247 --> 10:48.515
The food's good.

10:48.548 --> 10:50.517
Women are
distractingly attractive.

10:50.550 --> 10:52.252
Ugh, don't remind me.

10:52.252 --> 10:54.254
The Cubans are real.

10:54.254 --> 10:55.588
Glad you're enjoying yourself.

10:55.622 --> 10:57.390
This ain't no
friggin' vacation.

10:57.423 --> 10:59.492
I know, Charlie.
I'm just saying.

10:59.526 --> 11:00.627
Far as covers go,

11:00.660 --> 11:02.996
playing rich in Miami
ain't half bad.

11:02.996 --> 11:04.564
Is that a real Cuban?

11:08.401 --> 11:10.236
Nice.

11:10.270 --> 11:12.138
You know,
when you're pregnant,

11:12.138 --> 11:14.140
the booze, the smoke,
all the horrible shit

11:14.140 --> 11:16.509
you were happy
to consume yesterday,

11:16.543 --> 11:21.548
when you're thinking for two,
you won't touch it.

11:21.581 --> 11:24.484
We're so stupid, people.

11:24.517 --> 11:27.253
You would've been
a good mom, Chuck.

11:35.128 --> 11:37.263
(Charlie)
There's your guy.

11:37.297 --> 11:39.566
Remember, Germaine knows ATF
is covering his ass,

11:39.566 --> 11:42.135
so he's not gonna
be so easy to spook.

11:42.135 --> 11:44.137
And I guarantee
he's also gonna think--

11:44.137 --> 11:48.308
Charlie, I know how
to do my job, thank you.

11:48.341 --> 11:49.375
All right.

11:49.409 --> 11:51.244
TAC SUV's around the corner.

11:51.277 --> 11:52.579
- Mm-hmm.
- [chuckles]

11:52.612 --> 11:55.014
Be careful.

12:00.453 --> 12:01.688
It's all wrong, mate.

12:01.721 --> 12:03.189
What?

12:03.189 --> 12:05.325
Well, firstly, you don't come
into a cigar lounge

12:05.325 --> 12:06.326
with your own cigar.

12:06.326 --> 12:07.660
Put it out.

12:10.597 --> 12:12.599
Furthermore, you don't set
a meeting with me

12:12.632 --> 12:14.734
unless you've got a great big
pile of cash to move,

12:14.734 --> 12:17.303
which I know you don't.

12:17.337 --> 12:20.440
You're all sixes and sevens,
mate.

12:20.440 --> 12:22.575
You hear about the Windgates?

12:22.575 --> 12:24.310
Are you asking
whether I've heard

12:24.344 --> 12:26.312
if my clients
got pinched by the feds?

12:26.312 --> 12:28.047
Of course I have.

12:28.081 --> 12:30.149
They were
my income stream.

12:30.183 --> 12:31.718
You've got a problem,
don't you?

12:31.751 --> 12:33.086
Yeah, well,
I got a solution.

12:33.119 --> 12:34.621
I want to work for you.

12:34.654 --> 12:36.356
Now, hold on,
'cause I think I know

12:36.356 --> 12:38.191
how this conversation's
gonna go.

12:38.224 --> 12:41.427
You see, I would argue
that the Windgate bust

12:41.461 --> 12:44.097
puts you
in a very precarious situation.

12:44.130 --> 12:47.200
And if your name gets out,
it's bad for business.

12:47.233 --> 12:48.568
And you're gonna say,

12:48.601 --> 12:52.472
"Mate, if I was concerned
with coppers,

12:52.472 --> 12:56.309
what would I be doing
smoking baccy in Little Havana?"

12:56.342 --> 12:58.745
But I know two things.

12:58.745 --> 13:00.747
I know it took you three days
to get here

13:00.747 --> 13:02.148
when the Windgates
reached out,

13:02.181 --> 13:03.616
which means
you live abroad,

13:03.650 --> 13:06.085
and trips here
are risky.

13:06.085 --> 13:08.221
What else do you know?

13:08.221 --> 13:11.257
That you're
a hyperintelligent individual,

13:11.291 --> 13:14.494
that you understand acutely
that the heat's always on,

13:14.527 --> 13:16.329
and that every step
on U.S. soil

13:16.362 --> 13:18.531
could be your last
as a free man.

13:18.531 --> 13:20.967
So let me be your buffer,

13:20.967 --> 13:24.170
your boots on the ground
here in the States.

13:24.203 --> 13:28.574
If shit hits the fan,
I get sprayed.

13:28.608 --> 13:31.210
We both know...

13:31.244 --> 13:33.046
the fan's always spinning.

13:38.651 --> 13:43.456
♪ ♪

13:48.394 --> 13:50.563
[keys jingling]

13:50.563 --> 13:52.565
Wasn't sure you'd come.

13:52.565 --> 13:53.566
I said I'd be here.

13:53.566 --> 13:55.401
You say a lot of things.

13:55.401 --> 13:57.403
What are you implying?

13:57.437 --> 13:59.105
I've barely been able
to get you on the phone

13:59.138 --> 14:00.540
for the past couple weeks.

14:00.573 --> 14:01.674
You're avoiding me.

14:01.708 --> 14:03.343
No, no,
that's not it at all.

14:03.376 --> 14:05.111
I-I'm not.
I've just--

14:05.144 --> 14:06.412
I've been scattered at work

14:06.412 --> 14:10.149
and being sick, and...

14:10.149 --> 14:11.417
I'm sorry.

14:11.451 --> 14:12.685
I should have called.

14:12.719 --> 14:17.290
It's not like
I wasn't thinking about you.

14:17.290 --> 14:18.624
[keys jingle]

14:18.658 --> 14:20.693
You're tense.

14:20.727 --> 14:23.029
Yeah, well, you know,

14:23.029 --> 14:25.698
it's just always been Ari
next in line for this.

14:25.732 --> 14:27.767
It's a family nepotism thing.

14:27.967 --> 14:30.403
No one's considered my merit
for years.

14:30.436 --> 14:34.140
And now today,
getting here to these doors,

14:34.173 --> 14:38.044
it's been a--
it's been an uphill battle.

14:38.044 --> 14:41.047
Just take a breath, okay,

14:41.047 --> 14:43.049
and relax.

14:43.049 --> 14:45.284
You've earned this.

14:45.318 --> 14:48.521
And whatever uphill climb
you have,

14:48.554 --> 14:50.523
I will be by your side now.

14:53.459 --> 14:56.462
- [exhales]
- Yes.

14:56.496 --> 14:59.132
You look beautiful
in that dress.

14:59.165 --> 15:01.167
You wear that for me?

15:01.167 --> 15:03.169
Maybe.

15:03.169 --> 15:04.704
Toros...

15:04.737 --> 15:08.641
I don't just want to be
your arm candy.

15:08.674 --> 15:10.576
I know.

15:10.610 --> 15:12.612
What do you want?

15:16.349 --> 15:17.984
Everything.

15:25.725 --> 15:27.727
Bring what I told you?

15:30.730 --> 15:33.366
(Mike)
Why did Briggs need two of us
to watch Toros?

15:33.366 --> 15:34.700
(Tuturro)
I don't know.

15:34.734 --> 15:37.336
Stakeout's usually
a two-man job, right?

15:37.336 --> 15:40.606
What if I got
to piss or something?

15:40.640 --> 15:42.742
You're saying
you couldn't do this alone?

15:42.742 --> 15:44.744
I like having you here.

15:48.214 --> 15:49.215
Let me ask you something.

15:49.215 --> 15:50.750
What?

15:50.750 --> 15:53.085
Since the Sarkissian case
got handed to Briggs,

15:53.085 --> 15:56.088
what's been
his biggest obstacle?

15:56.122 --> 15:57.657
I don't know.
Ari, maybe?

15:57.690 --> 16:00.493
No, man, it's Logan.

16:00.526 --> 16:02.094
Logan's making him
finish this case

16:02.128 --> 16:03.362
no matter what happens.

16:03.396 --> 16:05.398
He told us that weeks ago.

16:05.398 --> 16:07.767
I mean, even if
he arrests Martun,

16:07.967 --> 16:09.168
Briggs is still
gonna get nailed

16:09.202 --> 16:11.971
for everything
that Ari's done.

16:12.004 --> 16:13.372
All right.

16:13.406 --> 16:14.574
What are you trying
to say, Mike?

16:14.607 --> 16:16.175
Yesterday Logan had me
in his office,

16:16.209 --> 16:18.244
and he asked me what I thought
Briggs was up to.

16:18.244 --> 16:19.745
It's like he could smell
something was off.

16:19.979 --> 16:21.347
Okay, but whatever,
that doesn't necessarily mean--

16:21.380 --> 16:22.615
And the plate,
it sounded like Briggs

16:22.648 --> 16:23.649
was giving Ari directions.

16:23.649 --> 16:25.084
Stop.

16:25.117 --> 16:26.519
Stop, look, I hear
what you're trying to say,

16:26.552 --> 16:30.590
but what are you
really saying?

16:30.623 --> 16:32.191
We're sitting here
doing surveillance on somebody

16:32.225 --> 16:34.527
who's not even a liability.

16:34.560 --> 16:37.029
[scoffs]

16:37.029 --> 16:40.233
Johnny, Briggs didn't
want us here to watch Toros.

16:40.266 --> 16:44.270
He wanted us here
so we wouldn't watch him.

16:44.270 --> 16:45.471
God damn it, man.

16:45.505 --> 16:48.140
You better be right,
Mike.

17:07.026 --> 17:09.061
You're late.

17:09.061 --> 17:12.031
Yeah, Ari,
the guy's strapped to a chair.

17:12.064 --> 17:14.967
I didn't exactly think
we were in a rush.

17:15.001 --> 17:16.536
Did you bring enough
for the rest of the class?

17:16.536 --> 17:18.471
That's a gourmet
ice cream sandwich.

17:18.504 --> 17:20.006
I paid $4.50 plus tax.

17:20.039 --> 17:21.641
- Get your own.
- Ah.

17:21.674 --> 17:24.176
Yeah, I'd rather do this
on an empty stomach anyway.

17:24.210 --> 17:25.278
You got power tools?

17:25.311 --> 17:27.280
Nah, man,
I'm old school.

17:27.313 --> 17:28.581
Hand tools only.

17:28.581 --> 17:30.716
I say we give this guy,
I don't know,

17:30.716 --> 17:32.718
a couple hours
with these toys.

17:32.752 --> 17:34.186
If he still doesn't
want to talk,

17:34.186 --> 17:35.588
maybe we run out and get
some of that stuff

17:35.588 --> 17:37.256
that Martun used on Colby.

17:40.059 --> 17:41.060
Acid, huh?

17:41.060 --> 17:42.261
Oh, yeah.

17:42.295 --> 17:44.530
I wouldn't mind
hearing this guy scream.

18:02.748 --> 18:05.718
[dogs barking]

18:07.520 --> 18:08.554
Can't lie.

18:08.588 --> 18:09.755
When you said
meet me at your office,

18:09.755 --> 18:11.090
I was expecting something

18:11.090 --> 18:14.060
a little more...upper crust.

18:14.093 --> 18:15.761
Well, I'm heartbroken it didn't
meet with your approval.

18:15.761 --> 18:17.229
You wanted to see
how I do business.

18:17.263 --> 18:19.632
This is it.

18:19.665 --> 18:22.001
How much you reckon
this house is worth?

18:22.034 --> 18:23.202
(Jakes)
I'd say 500 maybe.

18:23.235 --> 18:24.604
55 max.

18:24.604 --> 18:25.605
Yeah?

18:25.605 --> 18:27.340
I just paid 1.8 million for it.

18:27.340 --> 18:29.709
Sounds like
you got screwed.

18:29.742 --> 18:32.745
We'll see about that,
won't we?

18:35.181 --> 18:38.217
- Holy shit.
- You were saying?

18:38.217 --> 18:39.619
This whole house
is brimming with hard cash,

18:39.652 --> 18:41.988
most of it in the walls.

18:41.988 --> 18:43.656
My client estimates
its value at--

18:43.656 --> 18:45.391
2 million.

18:48.427 --> 18:49.629
You bought it for 1.8,

18:49.662 --> 18:51.397
minus the half a mil
it's actually worth,

18:51.397 --> 18:52.531
leaves 1.3,

18:52.531 --> 18:55.334
which is 2 million
minus your 35%.

18:55.368 --> 18:56.702
Your math is good.
That's a bonus.

18:56.736 --> 19:00.339
[banging]

19:00.373 --> 19:02.041
You paid well over
market value.

19:02.074 --> 19:05.077
Maybe some county clerk
clocks it, probably not.

19:05.111 --> 19:07.113
Either way, your client leaves
with $1.8 million,

19:07.113 --> 19:08.080
clean and accounted for,

19:08.114 --> 19:10.383
and you, my friend, you...

19:10.383 --> 19:12.652
Jesus Christ,
this is all your bounty.

19:12.652 --> 19:14.053
My bounty and my burden.

19:14.086 --> 19:16.389
Yeah, tell me how $2 million
is a burden.

19:16.389 --> 19:18.991
I'd like to know.

19:18.991 --> 19:20.993
Len...

19:21.027 --> 19:22.395
take the day off, mate.

19:22.395 --> 19:24.263
Take Zoe to the aquarium
or something.

19:24.296 --> 19:25.531
Thanks, Len.

19:31.103 --> 19:33.139
You got Len's job now.

19:33.139 --> 19:37.009
I ain't pitching myself
as a day laborer.

19:37.009 --> 19:38.444
I hope you're
wearing underwear.

19:44.550 --> 19:46.652
(Germaine)
My client, his name's Swiggy.

19:46.686 --> 19:48.020
I don't know
where he got a name like that,

19:48.020 --> 19:49.155
and frankly, I don't care.

19:49.155 --> 19:53.159
All I care about is his money.

19:53.159 --> 19:54.694
Swiggy brings in
about a million cash

19:54.694 --> 19:56.696
every three months.

19:56.696 --> 19:59.265
But since he trades
in hand-to-hand drug deals,

19:59.298 --> 20:01.133
pimping, and petty theft,

20:01.167 --> 20:04.136
most of his bills
are small denomination.

20:04.136 --> 20:07.406
2 million in small bills
weighs about 700 kilos.

20:07.440 --> 20:09.575
(Jakes)
How much is that in pounds?

20:09.608 --> 20:11.343
(Germaine)
A shit-ton.

20:14.580 --> 20:17.316
Once the cash is sorted,
tallied, strapped,

20:17.349 --> 20:19.585
set into something
more manageable,

20:19.585 --> 20:20.720
then it's just a matter
of getting it

20:20.720 --> 20:22.588
back out into society.

20:22.588 --> 20:26.425
[reggae music]

20:26.459 --> 20:28.728
That's where my little team
of Smurfs come in.

20:28.728 --> 20:30.996
They may not be
little blue men,

20:31.030 --> 20:33.265
but they are very, very loyal.

20:33.299 --> 20:34.400
Smurfs deliver cash

20:34.433 --> 20:36.302
to a number of front companies
I work with.

20:36.302 --> 20:38.304
Cash businesses, all of them,

20:38.304 --> 20:40.172
ones that can account
for a fresh influx

20:40.172 --> 20:44.677
of liquid capital...

20:44.710 --> 20:48.614
and ones just illicit enough
to not have any smart ideas.

20:48.614 --> 20:55.588
♪ ♪

20:55.621 --> 20:59.191
(Germaine)
Then the entire process
begins anew.

20:59.225 --> 21:01.093
A fresh house is purchased
by our friend Swiggy,

21:01.093 --> 21:05.765
and he begins filling it
with his dirty money.

21:05.998 --> 21:08.334
Everybody's richer.

21:08.334 --> 21:10.269
Everybody wins.

21:10.302 --> 21:13.706
♪ ♪

21:18.177 --> 21:22.348
Where's your friend?

21:22.348 --> 21:25.751
Well, he took off.

21:25.751 --> 21:27.486
He's running some errands.

21:27.486 --> 21:31.490
He's insane, Paul.

21:31.524 --> 21:34.126
Listen, Logan, um...

21:34.126 --> 21:37.396
let me ask you
a question.

21:37.429 --> 21:41.133
You remember what they used
on Colby?

21:41.167 --> 21:43.302
[breathing heavily]

21:43.335 --> 21:45.504
Paul...

21:45.504 --> 21:47.640
you got to call this in.

21:47.640 --> 21:50.609
I had enough.
I had enough.

21:52.478 --> 21:55.581
Now, you said
when I said the word,

21:55.614 --> 21:58.117
you'd pull me out.

21:58.150 --> 22:00.586
I'm saying the word, Paul.

22:00.619 --> 22:02.121
I'm saying the word.

22:02.121 --> 22:04.323
Now, listen to me.

22:04.356 --> 22:06.258
Listen to me.

22:09.995 --> 22:11.197
No.

22:13.432 --> 22:16.402
I've got a better idea.

22:16.402 --> 22:18.504
Paul.

22:18.537 --> 22:20.739
Paul, call it in.

22:20.973 --> 22:22.408
Don't do this.

22:22.408 --> 22:24.743
Paul, don't do it!

22:33.385 --> 22:38.023
Here will be Artsiv,
the eagle.

22:38.023 --> 22:41.160
He looks over
all Armenian people.

22:41.160 --> 22:44.163
It will show
that I am a protector.

22:44.163 --> 22:46.165
And what about that one?

22:46.165 --> 22:48.367
Here will be Arryutsy.

22:48.400 --> 22:50.469
He represents
the power of my king,

22:50.502 --> 22:52.638
of Martun.

22:52.671 --> 22:57.042
These are the same marks
that Tevan Adamian wears

22:57.042 --> 23:01.013
and other great men
that came before him.

23:01.046 --> 23:02.681
What about that mark?

23:02.715 --> 23:05.517
Oh, that's just--
that's just my--

23:11.323 --> 23:14.393
A gift from my father,

23:14.426 --> 23:17.429
for protecting my mother.

23:17.463 --> 23:19.465
You don't have
to talk about it.

23:19.465 --> 23:20.599
Sorry.

23:24.536 --> 23:28.307
Him beating her
was nothing new,

23:28.307 --> 23:29.308
but that night,

23:29.341 --> 23:33.712
he'd broken four bones
in her face.

23:33.979 --> 23:35.748
And he wasn't finished.

23:35.981 --> 23:37.716
Oh...

23:37.750 --> 23:42.087
I came at him with a knife,
but I was 11.

23:42.087 --> 23:43.355
Jesus.

23:43.389 --> 23:44.590
After he sobered up,

23:44.623 --> 23:48.093
Martun told him
to come back to his office

23:48.127 --> 23:51.463
to discuss
medical arrangements.

23:51.497 --> 23:55.067
No one ever saw him again.

23:55.100 --> 23:59.471
That day, I swore my life
to the Sarkissians.

23:59.471 --> 24:02.041
I may not be born
of their blood,

24:02.074 --> 24:06.011
but my loyalty to them,
to Martun...

24:10.649 --> 24:16.121
He gave my mother and I
a chance to start over,

24:16.121 --> 24:18.991
to trust.

24:19.024 --> 24:23.195
But every time
I look in the mirror,

24:23.228 --> 24:27.499
I have a reminder.

24:27.533 --> 24:30.102
- I better go get ready.
- Yeah.

24:33.505 --> 24:35.040
You can clean up here,
yes?

24:35.074 --> 24:36.241
Yeah.

24:47.386 --> 24:48.454
(Tuturro)
You still got any room

24:48.487 --> 24:50.255
for the benefit
of the doubt, man?

24:50.289 --> 24:53.325
'Cause I could sure
use some right about now.

24:56.662 --> 24:57.730
[sighs]

25:01.033 --> 25:02.668
If Logan even
makes it out of there,

25:02.668 --> 25:07.272
all he's gonna do is continue
to manipulate Briggs.

25:07.272 --> 25:09.141
If you had a problem
you couldn't fix,

25:09.141 --> 25:13.112
wouldn't you just try
to eliminate the problem?

25:13.145 --> 25:14.680
You talking about murder?

25:14.680 --> 25:17.416
Yeah.
Is that new for him?

25:18.450 --> 25:21.420
A bigwig at the FBI?

25:26.291 --> 25:27.393
I'm tired of sitting around

25:27.426 --> 25:28.660
and theorizing
about this shit, man.

25:28.694 --> 25:30.662
I'm going in.
Find out for my damn self.

25:30.696 --> 25:32.431
We just got to call
a team first, okay?

25:32.464 --> 25:33.766
We can't just
run up in there.

25:33.999 --> 25:35.968
Didn't you talk me
into coming here?

25:36.001 --> 25:38.537
This is Briggs.

25:38.537 --> 25:42.708
We don't know what's going on
in there, all right?

25:42.741 --> 25:44.543
No matter how good
your shot is, or mine,

25:44.576 --> 25:47.246
that guy is better.

25:47.279 --> 25:48.680
We got to have a team.

25:48.714 --> 25:50.049
[touch tones beeping]

25:50.049 --> 25:51.550
Don't know why you got me
in this shit, Mike, man.

25:51.583 --> 25:53.052
[line trills]

25:55.320 --> 25:57.589
You know,
back in the olden days,

25:57.589 --> 26:01.994
they would take
the severed hand of a dead man

26:02.027 --> 26:05.197
and turn it into a candle
with the fat from his body.

26:05.230 --> 26:09.168
It would be a hand,
but it would be on fire.

26:09.168 --> 26:12.571
It had magical powers,

26:12.571 --> 26:15.174
and it could unlock any door.

26:15.174 --> 26:19.011
They called it
"Hand of Glory."

26:19.044 --> 26:20.446
Mine is different.

26:20.446 --> 26:21.747
Still a burning hand,

26:21.747 --> 26:25.484
but it's gonna unlock
your fricking mouth hole.

26:25.484 --> 26:26.752
Hand of Glory.

26:26.985 --> 26:29.421
Ari, don't do this.

26:29.455 --> 26:32.724
You don't want to do this.

26:32.758 --> 26:34.226
Roll up his sleeve, guy.

26:34.259 --> 26:36.762
- Don't do it.
- With pleasure.

26:36.762 --> 26:41.233
Hey, uh, take it from me.

26:41.233 --> 26:44.069
You could save yourself
a lot of pain and misery,

26:44.103 --> 26:45.337
and you could save us
a lot of time

26:45.337 --> 26:49.074
if you would just
open up that mouth of yours

26:49.108 --> 26:51.743
and start talking.

26:51.977 --> 26:53.445
Well, what do you want me
to say?

26:53.479 --> 26:55.347
Just tell me
what you want me to say,

26:55.380 --> 26:56.448
and I'll say it.

26:56.482 --> 26:58.450
Colby was an informant.

26:58.484 --> 27:01.086
You tried to get him
to be an informant.

27:01.086 --> 27:04.123
Yes, I did.

27:04.123 --> 27:07.993
Who else are you hiding
in our organization?

27:07.993 --> 27:10.629
No one. There's no one else.
Who else would there be?

27:10.662 --> 27:13.532
- Tell me.
- There's nobody else.

27:13.532 --> 27:15.701
[screaming]

27:15.734 --> 27:18.504
[groaning]

27:18.537 --> 27:19.638
Just tell me who.

27:19.638 --> 27:20.973
[groaning]

27:20.973 --> 27:23.242
Spit it out.

27:23.242 --> 27:24.476
- No one.
- Spit it out!

27:24.510 --> 27:26.078
Nobody.
There's nobody else.

27:26.111 --> 27:27.112
Tell me who else!

27:27.146 --> 27:28.380
No one!

27:28.413 --> 27:29.982
Come on.

27:29.982 --> 27:31.183
[screaming]

27:31.216 --> 27:33.218
Oh, he smells.

27:33.252 --> 27:34.353
Oh.

27:34.386 --> 27:35.387
[whistles]

27:35.387 --> 27:36.688
Oh.

27:39.525 --> 27:42.661
Our Hand of Glory's
gonna touch your face now.

27:42.661 --> 27:44.363
I just want my family.

27:44.396 --> 27:46.532
I just want to see my family.

27:46.565 --> 27:48.534
Hear me?

27:48.567 --> 27:50.402
Gonna touch your face.

27:53.138 --> 27:55.407
The DEA!
The DEA!

27:55.407 --> 27:57.509
They have an agent under
with the Sarkissians.

27:57.543 --> 27:59.278
The DEA?

27:59.278 --> 28:02.281
Yes, Paige Arkin.
That's her name.

28:02.314 --> 28:04.283
She's a blonde.

28:04.316 --> 28:05.551
The lesbian?

28:05.551 --> 28:06.685
He's talking
about the freakin' lesbian.

28:06.685 --> 28:09.288
I don't know anybody else
named Paige, do you?

28:09.321 --> 28:10.522
[scoffs]

28:10.556 --> 28:12.558
Why would the DEA
have an agent under with us?

28:12.558 --> 28:14.560
She's tracking shipments
through Clear-Line,

28:14.593 --> 28:16.695
getting close to Toros.

28:16.728 --> 28:20.699
Mapping the Sarkissian pipeline,
all the ins and outs.

28:20.699 --> 28:23.669
Martun.

28:23.669 --> 28:25.537
She's trying
to take down Martun.

28:25.537 --> 28:28.307
Yes.

28:29.308 --> 28:31.310
Holy shit.

28:31.343 --> 28:33.278
This is fricking bad, guy.

28:33.312 --> 28:35.314
Yeah, if we believe him.

28:35.314 --> 28:37.716
He knows her name.
He knows Clear-Line.

28:37.716 --> 28:40.185
He knows
she's cuddled up with Toros.

28:40.219 --> 28:41.186
Yeah.

28:41.220 --> 28:42.688
And the fricking
ceremony, guy.

28:42.721 --> 28:43.689
What?

28:43.722 --> 28:44.690
Toros' ceremony.

28:44.723 --> 28:48.560
He invited the DEA bitch
to his ceremony.

28:48.594 --> 28:50.062
She's probably there
right now.

28:50.062 --> 28:52.698
And you said Martun and Tev
were gonna be there.

28:52.731 --> 28:54.066
I got to call them.

28:54.099 --> 28:55.534
- Call who?
- Toros.

28:55.567 --> 28:57.035
Call your uncle, Ari.

28:57.035 --> 28:59.171
If Toros can't handle
that bitch, what can he handle?

28:59.171 --> 29:00.539
Listen, Toros
is the only thing

29:00.572 --> 29:02.407
standing between
you and Martun.

29:02.441 --> 29:03.709
That ceremony
that's happening today,

29:03.742 --> 29:05.644
those tattoos
that he's getting,

29:05.677 --> 29:08.280
they should be on your skin,
man, not his.

29:08.313 --> 29:10.082
Tev and Martun
feel differently.

29:10.082 --> 29:11.750
Oh, yeah, well,
how would Tev and Martun feel

29:11.750 --> 29:13.218
if they knew that
he was working with a fed?

29:13.218 --> 29:15.487
I told you
what you wanted to hear.

29:15.487 --> 29:17.356
Shut up!

29:17.389 --> 29:18.757
Listen to me, Ari.

29:18.757 --> 29:20.759
Maybe this is
an honest mistake,

29:20.993 --> 29:22.728
and maybe, just maybe,

29:22.761 --> 29:24.363
Toros is
selling you guys out.

29:24.363 --> 29:26.331
But you know
what the good news is?

29:26.365 --> 29:29.401
He'll never be
second in command now.

29:32.471 --> 29:35.440
[dramatic music]

29:35.474 --> 29:44.349
♪ ♪

29:44.349 --> 29:47.219
Tev was on the way to the church
when he got my call.

29:47.252 --> 29:49.288
Another ten minutes,
and Martun would have been

29:49.321 --> 29:52.090
in the same room
with a DEA agent.

29:52.124 --> 29:54.493
You did good today,
my guy.

29:54.526 --> 29:56.395
Tev wants us
to go get Toros

29:56.395 --> 29:57.629
and bring him here.

29:57.663 --> 29:59.364
Hmm, sounds good.

29:59.398 --> 30:01.066
Go get him.

30:04.102 --> 30:05.971
I'm gonna tie up
a loose end.

30:06.004 --> 30:07.105
Hey, whoa, whoa!

30:07.105 --> 30:08.073
Hey, wait!

30:08.106 --> 30:10.208
[gunshots]

30:11.410 --> 30:13.378
We got to go now.

30:13.412 --> 30:15.380
Hold, hold, hold, hold on.

30:15.414 --> 30:18.250
- Ari's coming out on foot.
- Shit.

30:18.250 --> 30:19.251
Shit.

30:19.251 --> 30:20.385
What do we do?

30:20.385 --> 30:21.720
Take half the team,
follow him,

30:21.753 --> 30:23.989
take him down.

30:23.989 --> 30:26.491
What about Briggs?

30:26.525 --> 30:27.492
Ah, damn it.

30:27.526 --> 30:28.660
All right, B team,
come with me.

30:28.694 --> 30:30.095
We're gonna follow the Chrysler

30:30.128 --> 30:31.129
southbound
toward Los Angeles.

30:31.163 --> 30:32.431
Alpha, you're with me.

30:32.431 --> 30:34.666
Suspect Agent Paul Briggs
may be armed and dangerous.

30:34.700 --> 30:36.601
We may have a body.

30:44.543 --> 30:45.077
It's quite the turnout.

30:46.511 --> 30:48.747
That's good, right?

30:48.980 --> 30:51.283
They were expecting this
to be Ari.

30:51.316 --> 30:54.152
I can see it
on their faces.

30:54.152 --> 30:55.354
And where the hell is Tev?

30:55.387 --> 30:56.655
Okay, here, come here.

30:56.688 --> 30:59.491
Hey, listen to me.

30:59.524 --> 31:02.260
They may have been
expecting Ari,

31:02.294 --> 31:05.664
but who they got
is so much greater.

31:05.697 --> 31:09.501
You made everybody in this room
realize your strength.

31:09.534 --> 31:11.002
Do you know how much
I admire that?

31:11.036 --> 31:12.070
Hmm?

31:12.104 --> 31:15.507
Do you know how rare that is?

31:15.540 --> 31:21.012
I want a man
who takes what he wants.

31:21.046 --> 31:23.148
You're exactly what I need.

31:23.181 --> 31:24.449
Thank you.

31:24.449 --> 31:25.717
[phone buzzing]

31:25.717 --> 31:27.152
Sorry.

31:27.185 --> 31:30.055
[buzzing continues]

31:30.055 --> 31:31.723
Just give me a second.

31:31.723 --> 31:33.325
Thanks.

31:36.461 --> 31:37.729
(Paige)
How's Logan?

31:37.729 --> 31:40.065
You need to go.

31:40.065 --> 31:42.634
It--it's less than an hour
to the ceremony.

31:42.667 --> 31:44.369
I understand that,
but Logan gave you up.

31:44.403 --> 31:47.005
You're burned.

31:47.038 --> 31:48.006
What?

31:48.039 --> 31:49.007
(Briggs)
Burned.

31:49.040 --> 31:50.375
Tevan Adamian knows you're DEA.

31:50.409 --> 31:52.144
Soon Toros is gonna know.

31:52.177 --> 31:56.047
You need to get
out of there now.

31:56.081 --> 31:57.616
- I--
- Hey.

31:57.616 --> 31:59.751
Hey.

31:59.985 --> 32:00.752
Everything okay?

32:00.986 --> 32:03.021
Yeah.

32:03.054 --> 32:04.756
Yeah, I'm just...

32:04.756 --> 32:06.158
I'm gonna go to the washroom

32:06.191 --> 32:09.327
and just freshen up
before everything starts.

32:09.361 --> 32:10.629
Okay.

32:25.977 --> 32:29.080
[cell phone ringing]

32:29.114 --> 32:33.018
[speaks Armenian]
Tevan.

32:33.051 --> 32:36.455
Yes, I'm here.

32:36.488 --> 32:37.589
Yes, she's here.

32:41.293 --> 32:43.395
Leaving? No.
Why would we go anywhere?

32:43.395 --> 32:44.763
No, we'll be here.

32:44.996 --> 32:46.398
Yes, both of us.

32:49.100 --> 32:51.603
Okay, I look forward
to seeing you.

32:59.010 --> 33:00.612
[knocking]

33:00.645 --> 33:03.114
(Toros)
Paige, I just got a call
from Tevan.

33:03.114 --> 33:06.384
He's actually excited
to meet you.

33:06.384 --> 33:08.487
How crazy is--

33:08.520 --> 33:10.322
Paige.

33:21.433 --> 33:23.134
[grunts]

33:23.168 --> 33:24.135
I'm so sorry, Logan.

33:24.169 --> 33:26.538
(Mike)
Don't move.

33:26.538 --> 33:28.073
- Mike?
- Briggs.

33:28.106 --> 33:29.374
(Mike)
Let me see your hands.

33:29.407 --> 33:30.475
Mike, what are you
doing here?

33:30.509 --> 33:31.676
Back away from the body.

33:31.676 --> 33:35.413
- Warren, what are you--
- Back away.

33:35.413 --> 33:37.148
[Logan coughing]

33:37.148 --> 33:40.285
Agent Warren.

33:40.285 --> 33:43.121
What the hell is this?

33:43.154 --> 33:44.489
Sir...

33:47.025 --> 33:48.293
Hey, speed up.

33:48.326 --> 33:50.028
I don't want this asshole
to see us coming.

33:50.028 --> 33:51.530
[engine revving]

33:51.563 --> 33:53.131
Sir, are you okay?

33:53.164 --> 33:57.002
No, Warren,
I'm not nearly okay.

33:57.035 --> 33:59.604
Agents, stand down.

33:59.638 --> 34:01.039
Mike, you want to tell me

34:01.072 --> 34:04.709
what the hell
you're doing here?

34:04.709 --> 34:06.711
You put me on Toros
so that you could--

34:06.711 --> 34:09.581
So that I could what?

34:09.614 --> 34:12.417
God damn it, Mike, would you
please put the gun away,

34:12.450 --> 34:13.685
unless you're gonna shoot me?

34:13.718 --> 34:15.320
Pull out your cell phone
and call Johnny.

34:15.353 --> 34:17.188
Tell him that Paige
has been burned.

34:17.188 --> 34:19.057
- What?
- Burned.

34:19.090 --> 34:20.425
Her cover is blown, okay?

34:20.458 --> 34:22.694
He needs to stick tight to Toros
in case he tries to follow her.

34:22.727 --> 34:24.696
(Logan)
I didn't go through
all this shit for nothing.

34:24.729 --> 34:26.464
Warren, do it now.

34:28.233 --> 34:30.168
Johnny's following Ari
to arrest him.

34:30.201 --> 34:31.536
What the--

34:35.307 --> 34:37.175
I need a walkie now.

34:37.175 --> 34:39.044
Give it here.

34:39.077 --> 34:41.446
This is Special Agent in Charge
Sean Logan.

34:41.446 --> 34:45.350
I am ordering you,
do not engage Ari Adamian.

34:45.350 --> 34:49.087
I repeat,
do not engage Ari Adamian.

34:49.087 --> 34:50.755
You're kidding me, man.

34:50.755 --> 34:53.091
Can I ask you
a question, Mike?

34:53.091 --> 34:54.626
Who's on Toros?

34:54.659 --> 34:56.761
- Nobody.
- Nobody.

34:56.761 --> 34:58.496
Would you please
get the car now?

34:58.496 --> 35:00.732
All right, let's move.

35:00.765 --> 35:02.100
Briggs.

35:02.133 --> 35:04.035
What?

35:04.069 --> 35:06.671
I want you to know
that nothing changes.

35:06.705 --> 35:10.175
This still ends
with you burning.

35:13.244 --> 35:14.746
Paul, I just got home.

35:14.980 --> 35:17.616
What the hell happened?
Call me back.

35:17.616 --> 35:20.619
[dramatic music]

35:20.652 --> 35:28.226
♪ ♪

35:28.259 --> 35:30.595
Didn't think I'd come.

35:33.531 --> 35:37.335
Toros.

35:37.369 --> 35:38.637
Gonna let me in, or...

35:38.670 --> 35:41.039
do you want to play
more mind games?

35:52.384 --> 35:54.066
[thumping club music]

35:55.353 --> 36:03.328
♪ ♪

36:16.708 --> 36:18.343
He's trying to grab the rope.

36:18.376 --> 36:20.278
He's flapping around
and whatnot.

36:20.311 --> 36:22.647
You know, so he's kind of like--
like a dog,

36:22.681 --> 36:24.215
when you grab him up
by the collar

36:24.249 --> 36:26.217
and he can't breathe,
you know what I'm saying?

36:26.251 --> 36:27.552
But Trina here--

36:27.552 --> 36:29.220
Trina, what was that you said?

36:29.254 --> 36:32.691
She says, "Cut him down.
He's strangulating!"

36:32.691 --> 36:34.125
[laughs]

36:34.159 --> 36:36.227
Yeah, I cut him down,
all right,

36:36.261 --> 36:38.163
right after he shit his pants.

36:38.196 --> 36:40.699
And I still ain't give him
the rock neither.

36:40.732 --> 36:44.536
Nothing more fun
than a basehead, right?

36:44.536 --> 36:47.105
All right, pal?

36:47.138 --> 36:49.674
Swiggy, I believe you know
my friend Dale.

36:49.708 --> 36:50.675
What's up, my brother?

36:50.709 --> 36:52.577
I don't think
we formally met.

36:55.447 --> 36:56.715
Right, well, I will leave you

36:56.715 --> 36:58.283
to the festivities,
my friend.

36:58.316 --> 37:00.318
Cheers.
Thanks for the party.

37:00.318 --> 37:01.986
No doubt.

37:12.197 --> 37:14.165
I don't know how
you work for that guy.

37:14.199 --> 37:15.433
Scum.

37:15.467 --> 37:18.036
Yeah, he's
right proper scum.

37:18.036 --> 37:20.171
But tonight,
this is his boat,

37:20.205 --> 37:22.107
and he's your host.

37:22.140 --> 37:26.444
Besides, he's a vital part
of this ecosystem.

37:26.444 --> 37:28.546
Without him,
none of this exists.

37:28.580 --> 37:31.549
Without him, a lot
of stereotypes don't exist.

37:33.985 --> 37:36.020
[camera shutter clicking]

37:38.757 --> 37:42.761
You think I'm having a laugh,
but I'm not.

37:42.994 --> 37:46.331
Men like me cleaned
bootlegging money from the Micks

37:46.364 --> 37:48.633
and created the Kennedys.

37:48.633 --> 37:50.735
The goombahs laundered
racket money

37:50.969 --> 37:52.470
from the mob and built Vegas.

37:52.504 --> 37:53.705
And Miami, all of this,

37:53.738 --> 37:57.575
that's cocaine money
from the Latins.

37:57.609 --> 37:59.077
That's what I love
about this business.

37:59.077 --> 38:00.745
Doesn't matter
where you're from.

38:00.979 --> 38:04.282
Any man can build a kingdom.

38:22.000 --> 38:24.068
What am I doing here?

38:24.102 --> 38:26.371
What are you doing here?

38:26.371 --> 38:31.176
You climb out
from the window.

38:31.209 --> 38:32.210
You know what?

38:32.243 --> 38:33.511
I wouldn't even be here,

38:33.511 --> 38:37.649
but Tevan called
asking for you.

38:37.682 --> 38:39.117
You spoke to Tev?

38:39.117 --> 38:41.386
Yeah, we're supposed to be
meeting him

38:41.419 --> 38:42.987
outside of the church,

38:42.987 --> 38:46.991
like...now.

38:46.991 --> 38:49.527
Can we go?

38:49.527 --> 38:50.662
Toros, I can't.

38:50.662 --> 38:52.297
- What?
- I--

38:52.330 --> 38:54.532
I'm not Armenian.

38:54.566 --> 38:55.700
I'm not part of your family.

38:55.733 --> 38:58.269
I'm not even
in your close circle of friends.

38:58.303 --> 39:02.240
Tev will know that
the moment he meets me.

39:02.273 --> 39:03.374
I am an outsider.

39:03.408 --> 39:05.243
I can't be there.

39:05.276 --> 39:06.544
You're an outsider?

39:06.578 --> 39:08.346
That's how you feel?
An outsider?

39:08.379 --> 39:09.347
No, look--

39:09.380 --> 39:11.416
I welcomed you in.

39:11.416 --> 39:15.620
I opened the door,
and I let you in!

39:15.653 --> 39:16.754
How are you an outsider?

39:16.988 --> 39:18.223
What are you saying
to me right now?

39:18.256 --> 39:19.157
That is not what I'm saying.

39:19.190 --> 39:20.758
After all the trust,

39:20.992 --> 39:24.028
after all of the things
that I told you,

39:24.028 --> 39:27.632
that I swear to God
I've never told anyone,

39:27.665 --> 39:32.537
you left me there
in a church by myself.

39:32.570 --> 39:37.041
That is not what--
I am so sorry.

39:37.041 --> 39:39.043
I did what I thought
was best for you.

39:39.043 --> 39:42.447
I did what I thought
was best for us.

39:42.447 --> 39:44.649
Okay, you have to trust me.

39:44.682 --> 39:45.984
Trust you?

39:46.017 --> 39:47.318
Stop bullsh--

39:47.352 --> 39:50.288
[grunting]

39:51.556 --> 39:53.725
(Briggs)
Come on, Paige, come on,
come on, come on.

39:53.725 --> 39:56.427
Voicemail, she's not picking up,
man, God damn it!

39:56.461 --> 39:58.596
Bro, can you please
drive faster?

39:58.630 --> 40:01.599
[engine revving]

40:01.599 --> 40:04.035
[beeping]

40:04.035 --> 40:06.571
[tires squealing]

40:08.706 --> 40:10.308
Just drive, Mike.

40:15.213 --> 40:20.018
Don't talk to me
about trust!

40:20.051 --> 40:21.452
You've been bullshitting me.

40:21.486 --> 40:24.489
Since the very beginning,
you've been bullshitting me.

40:24.522 --> 40:27.458
The most important day
of my life,

40:27.492 --> 40:30.094
- and you got me here--
- Ah!

41:26.150 --> 41:28.519
[dog barks]
